      <p><img class=large src="doug.jpg" width=200 height=200 style="float:left; display:block;margin:0 20px 0 0px" alt="Headshot of Doug Fellows"> 
Your Uncle Gary Parsons was kind enough to speak to you about me and told me to come cold into your office today but I prefer to introduce myself.

      <p>My name is Douglas Rae Fellows. My applications for work are not being accepted fast enough. I am looking for temporary minimum after taxes $500/month, preferably $1350/month employment starting as soon as possible. I was born at the Haywood County hospital, Waynesville, North Carolina, Sunday, June 30th, 1957. I would like to work for you.
        
      <p>June 2013 to June 2019 I worked full-time for AJ Ellis, your cousin by law?, in Bolivar, MO, repairing the ~56 homes and ~100 apartments he owns or was responsible for and bought his parts and supplies online. The last job I did for him was to repair the transmission drive shaft of a commercial laundry washing machine. In my entire life the only thing I can remember to pay someone else to repair for me was a car radiator. I have a valid Missouri drivers license, a clean driving record, what I do not know how to repair I know how to Google and live across the street from the university. My father graduated from Southwest Baptist College in 1939. I can work un-supervised, need no training, have my own tools, though I prefer to use yours, and will tell you if my work needs to be signed off on.
        
      <p>I am a member of the First Baptist Church of Wheaton, Maryland and have voted in every United States presidential election since 1976.
        
